## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of recent data and the complexity of isolating the impact of terrorism from other factors affecting global trade. Additionally, the studies reviewed may not cover all regions equally, potentially skewing the findings towards more documented areas. Further research is needed to explore the long-term effects of terrorism on trade and the effectiveness of policy responses.